The paper deals with the task of age group and gender estimation from face images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of pre-training on ImageNet, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the Adience benchmark, which is a dataset commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) research for age and gender estimation.
